HEADWORD: stator
<hw>sta"tor</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"t⟦etil⟧r; st⟦acr⟧t"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>A stationary part in or about
which another part (the rotor) revolves, esp. when both are large;</def>
<specif>as,</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The stationary
member of an electrical machine, as of an induction motor.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Steam Turbine)</fld> <def>The case inclosing a
turbine wheel; the body of stationary blades or nozzles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

